entry.tran: 不能想象的;不可思议的
entry.def: If you describe something as inconceivable, you think it is very unlikely to happen or be true.

example.ex: It was inconceivable to me that Toby could have been my attacker...
example.tran: 真想不到托比竟会是袭击我的人。

example.ex: Until now, a devaluation of the dollar seemed inconceivable.
example.tran: 直到现在,美元的贬值似乎都无法想象。
